[ Steps ]

- Get the last 10 ns of aa simulation: last-10ns.xtc
- Make the molecules whole: trjconv -f last-10ns.xtc -o whole.xtc -s mem-md.tpr -pbc whole   (choose system)
      - mem-md.tpr is the file generated by grompp (gromacs) that has all the information necessary to run mdrun (start the simulation of MD)
- Run the script that does the mapping: ./traj.sh
      - topol.top : topology for aa system
      - mdout.mdp : simulation specifications (time, time step, temperature, pressure, type of thermostat and barostat, stuff like this)
      - mem-md-100.gro : final configuration of the system (100 ns)
- Generate an executable for the fortran code to rename the beads: gfortran rename.f90 -o rename
- Run it: ./rename
- Generate the density profile: python3 hymd_optimize.py plot --traj aa-traj.xtc --top frame90ns.gro --skip-first 0 --resolution types --bins 100 --no-marker --range 8 --ignore "all" "solvent" "name:.*" "lipid:.*" "ions" "type:D" --symmetrize